{"id":"roman-numeral","slug":"roman-numeral","name":"Roman Numeral Converter","category":"math","icon":"Ⅻ","description":"Convert Arabic numbers to Roman numerals and understand the Roman numeral system.","tags":["roman numeral","convert","math","history"],"fields":[{"id":"number","label":"Arabic Number","type":"number","defaultValue":2024,"constraint":{"min":1,"max":3999,"step":1}},{"id":"thousands","label":"Thousands digit (M)","type":"computed","precision":0,"helpText":"Number of M symbols needed"},{"id":"hundreds","label":"Hundreds digit","type":"computed","precision":0},{"id":"tens","label":"Tens digit","type":"computed","precision":0},{"id":"ones","label":"Ones digit","type":"computed","precision":0}],"groups":[{"id":"inputs","label":"Number","fields":["number"]},{"id":"outputs","label":"Breakdown","fields":["thousands","hundreds","tens","ones"]}],"formulas":{"thousands":"floor(number/1000)","hundreds":"floor(mod(number,1000)/100)","tens":"floor(mod(number,100)/10)","ones":"mod(number,10)"},"explanation":"## Roman Numerals\n\n| Symbol | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| I | 1 |\n| V | 5 |\n| X | 10 |\n| L | 50 |\n| C | 100 |\n| D | 500 |\n| M | 1000 |\n\nSubtraction rule: IV=4, IX=9, XL=40, XC=90, CD=400, CM=900","examples":[{"label":"2024","inputs":{"number":2024}},{"label":"42","inputs":{"number":42}},{"label":"1999","inputs":{"number":1999}}]}
